{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, ML leads to a more flexible prediction.",
    "Although previous studies made predictions at individual points, Lilienkamp et al. (2022) achieved \"areal\" prediction by treating the explanatory and predictive variables as map-shaped data.",
    "Rekoske et al. (2023) presented a reduced-order modeling approach based on interpolated proper orthogonal decomposition to predict the spatial distribution of peak ground velocity.",
    "Sreenath and Raghukanth (2023) constructed a ground-motion model based on the Bayesian Neural Network (BNN) (Jospin et al. 2022), in which the Bayesian framework is incorporated into neural networks.",
    "Their approach could enable the evaluation of uncertainties in the prediction of earthquake motion because BNN facilitates probabilistic prediction."
  ]
}